FINALLY DONE >_< so time consuming. (yes i know theres a couple doubles... like 10 my bad)

Nice upload, my download speed stayed over 1 MB/s almost the whole time, I'll seed at least 200%.

There are 23 (out of 703 total) problem files though, windows can't see what their bit rate or other idv3 tags and can't set info like genre, however, it seems that anything that isn't windows gui, such as itunes or vlc can set the info just fine.

Setting the info with another program doesn't fix the broken metadata, I'll update if I find a method other than reconverting the "broken" files back to mp3 to fix this.

To anyone who reads my comment, this "broken" metadata is only broken to windows, it should work just fine on an mp3 player or in any other media player.
